ion/Basic.lean#L148-L170"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/MonoidLocalization/Basic.html#AddLocalization.r\"><span class=\"name\">AddLocalization</span>.<span class=\"name\">r</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommMonoid\">AddCommMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Submonoid/Defs.html#AddSubmonoid\">AddSubmonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/Congruence/Defs.html#AddCon\">AddCon</a> (<span class=\"fn\">M</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The congruence relation on `M × S`, `M` an `AddCommMonoid` and `S` an `AddSubmonoid` of `M`,\nwhose quotient is the localization of `M` at `S`, defined as the unique congruence relation on\n`M × S` such that for any other congruence relation `s` on `M × S` where for all `y ∈ S`,\n`(0, 0) ∼ (y, y)` under `s`, we have that `(x₁, y₁) ∼ (x₂, y₂)` by `r` implies\n`(x₁, y₁) ∼ (x₂, y₂)` by `s`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/MonoidLocalization/Basic.html#AddLocalization.r","kind":"def","line":139,"name":"AddLocalization.r","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/MonoidLocalization/Basic.lean#L139-L144"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/MonoidLocalization/Basic.html#Localization.r\"><span class=\"name\">Localization</span>.<span class=\"name\">r</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#CommMonoid\">CommMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Submonoid/Defs.html#Submonoid\">Submonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/Congruence/Defs.html#Con\">Con</a> (<span class=\"fn\">M</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">S</span></span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The congruence relation on `M × S`, `M` a `CommMonoid` and `S` a submonoid of `M`, whose\nquotient is the localization of `M` at `S`, defined as the unique congruence relation on\n`M × S` such that for any other congruence relation `s` on `M × S` where for all `y ∈ S`,\n`(1, 1) ∼ (y, y)` under `s`, we have that `(x₁, y₁) ∼ (x₂, y₂)` by `r` implies\n`(x₁, y₁) ∼ (x₂, y₂)` by `s`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/MonoidLocalization/Basic.html#Localization.r","kind":"def","line":134,"name":"Localization.r","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/MonoidLocalization/Basic.lean#L134-L146"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_wit